						"text" : "This project will seek to convince young people to get involved and speak their mind â€œsema usikikeâ€� through the use of the SMS Interface Platform. This platform offers the opportunity for youth to give feedback on what is happening around them and what would inform their decision making come 2012 elections.\r\n\r\nThe activities under this output will include:\r\n\r\nPublicity through social media\r\nInformation to show how the SMS Interface Platform works will be disseminated on online platforms which so as to ensure that correct information is delivered both ways. \r\n\r\nIEC materials\r\n2000 copies of brochures and stickers will be produced and distributed to also assist in giving any other information regarding the SMS Interface Platform.\r\n\r\nYAA Network\r\nYAA will also endavoure to work with and through other platforms that will ensure maximum dissemination of information about the shortcode. These efforts will also be carried out to promote buy-in of the Platform by the general citizens. \r\n\r\nLocal Media Campaign\r\nThe aim of the local media campaign is the similar to the use of the brochures â€“ to raise awareness of the use of the SMS Platform â€“ though the media campaign would reach a wider audience. This will include Talk-shows in mainstream and Community Radio Shows, Press Conferences, press releases on feedback reports. \r\n"
