						"text" : "The primary outcome of this referral service is to increase the uptake of ARH services. SnapshotÂ® will\r\ncollect data from the health facilities.\r\nThe data collected will primarily comprise of the numbers of adolescents served for HIV, STI and family\r\nplanning services. Data on the numbers of adolescents collecting condoms, HIV counselling and testing,\r\ncontraceptive services and treatment of STIs will be collected. The purpose of this data is to establish the:\r\na) number of adolescents attending the health facility for general health\r\nb) number of adolescents attending health facility for HIV, STI, pregnancy prevention (including\r\nnumbers of condoms, VCT, and postâ€�abortion care)\r\nc) number of adolescents attending health facility for HIV and STI treatment\r\nd) number of adolescent pregnancies (unwanted and underâ€�age)\r\ne) number of adolescents attending health facility for other contraceptives (the pill, IUD, injection,\r\nfemale condom, sterilisation â€“ where available)\r\nf) number of adolescents attending health facility testing HIV +ve/â€�ve (where there is a testing\r\nservice)\r\ng) number of adolescents attending facilities to test for specific STIs (where there is a testing service)\r\nh) prevalence (and/or incidence) of HIV and STIs on the data above\r\ni) any other emerging ARH outcome measure associated with uptake of RH services\r\n"
