		"description" : [{
				"@" : {
					"xml:lang" : "en",
					"type" : "1"
				},
				"text" : "The project aims to reduce HIV/AIDS stigma and discrimination and build capacity for church community care of PLWHA in 10 Lagos local government areas. Key faith-based community influencers will have skills and capacity to be effective leaders for community action against HIV/AIDS stigma and discrimination. Church leaders will form a network in 10 lGAs to coordinate an anti S&D campaign and foster community-based care and support. Duty bearers will be made aware of the need to strengthen action against S&D. 90% of targeted church communities will offer non-stigmatising community care. Rates of voluntary testing and disclosure of status will increase in the 10 LGAs. Beneficiaries: PLWHA who experience discrimination and lack of community-based services."
			}
		],
